---
title: One-Pan Cheeseburger Lettuce Wraps with Crispy Fried Onions, Pickles & Special Sauce
description: How do you make a cheeseburger more fun? Skip the bun! These lettuce wraps feature all the classic burger fixin’s you love, stuffed inside romaine for a crunchy twist. First, ground beef is cooked with melty cheddar, then the filling is nestled into lettuce leaves and topped with crispy fried onions, chopped pickles, and special sauce. Yep, this lettuce wrap is one of those things you’ll have to see to be-leaf!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-cheeseburger-lettuce-wraps-190a726c.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/one-pan-cheeseburger-lettuce-wraps-62a7595a99a090d3990ca1f6-344d13a7.pdf
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 720 kcal
  fat: 53 g
  saturated fat: 21 g
  carbohydrates: 24 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
course: main course
time required: 15 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-cheeseburger-lettuce-wraps-62a7595a99a090d3990ca1f6
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Thinly slice 1-2
small center leaves until you have 1/3 cup shredded lettuce (2/3 cup for 4 servings).
Drain @dill pickle{1%sliced}; roughly chop.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @ketchup{2%tablespoon},
half the @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon}, and 1/2 tsp @fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}
(you'll use more in the next step). (For 4 servings, use all the mustard and
1 tsp Fry Seasoning.) Stir in @water{1%tsp} at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling
consistency. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, remaining Fry Seasoning, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.
Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and almost cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings).
Cook, stirring, until liquid has absorbed and beef is cooked through,
~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Add half the @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}; stir until melted, ~{1%minute} (save the
rest for serving).

Divide lettuce leaves between plates. Fill with beef mixture, pickle,
shredded lettuce, @crispy fried onions{1}, remaining cheese, and special
sauce. Serve.